sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K985001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is an assembly of a promoter, a fluorescent protein (brighter than standard GFP), and an ssra degradation tag. It is useful in biosensors to detect the presence of copper ions. Based on a Tinkercell model, the activation of this part can result from as little as 1.3 ppm, and can cause a several micromolar increase in FP production.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jackson Allen
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Combination of TagRFP, sara degradation sequence, and Copper-inducible promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Please see 2013hs.igem.org/Team:NC_School_of_Sci_Math for in-depth design information.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Hin LVA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: DNA invertase Hin tagged with LVA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part produces the Hin protein with an LVA degredation tag. We are currently looking into this as a way to ensure no Hin is floating around once we turn off the Hin promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erin Zwack, Sabriya Rosemond
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Salmonella typhimurium and the the Hin part without LVA.
